const DocsApi = () => (
  <>
    <DocH1>API reference</DocH1>
    <DocH2>WebSocket protocol</DocH2>
    <DocP>
      Two channels per connection — fast (optimistic, sub-ms) and final (BFT-confirmed, ~4ms).
      Wire format is MessagePack in production, JSON in dev.
    </DocP>
    <DocCode>{`// Authenticate
{ "op": "auth", "lei": "...", "desk": "ECM-147", "signed_nonce": "..." }

// Subscribe to order book
{ "op": "sub", "channel": "book", "symbol": "BTC-PERP" }

// Place order
{
  "op": "place_order",
  "client_oid": "c-12345",
  "symbol": "BTC-PERP",
  "side": "buy",
  "type": "limit",
  "price": 98000.0,
  "size": 0.5,
  "leverage": 10,
  "tif": "GTC",
  "reduce_only": false,
  "post_only": false
}

// Optimistic ack (you receive on /ws/fast ~0.8ms later)
{
  "op": "order_ack",
  "client_oid": "c-12345",
  "order_id": "ob-...",
  "seq": 194820191,
  "status": "pending",
  "latency_us": 803
}

// Final confirmation (you receive on /ws/final ~4ms later)
{
  "op": "order_final",
  "client_oid": "c-12345",
  "order_id": "ob-...",
  "block_height": 4892341,
  "chain_id": 3,
  "fills": [ { "fill_id": "...", "price": 98000.0, "size": 0.5, ... } ]
}`}</DocCode>

    <DocH2>REST endpoints</DocH2>
    <DocP>
      REST is for non-latency-sensitive operations: historical data, account snapshots,
      regulatory report downloads. Base URL: <span style={{ color: COLORS.mint }}>https://api.onyx.jpmorgan.com/v1</span>
    </DocP>
    <DocCode>{`GET  /account/{desk}                  Account summary + balances
GET  /account/{desk}/positions        Open positions across all instruments
GET  /account/{desk}/orders           All orders (filter with ?status=open|filled|...)
GET  /account/{desk}/fills            Fill history (paginate with ?before=<ts>)
GET  /trades/{symbol}?limit=100       Public trade tape

GET  /instruments                     All listed instruments + specs
GET  /chain/{id}/status               Per-chain health, TPS, last block
GET  /funding/{symbol}/history        Historical funding rates

POST /account/{desk}/cancel-all       Panic button — cancels every open order`}</DocCode>

    <DocH2>Authentication</DocH2>
    <DocP>
      mTLS at the transport layer using your desk's X.509 certificate. Application-layer
      proof-of-possession via signed nonce (Ed25519 signature of timestamp + session ID).
      REST reuses the same mTLS session — there is no bearer-token fallback.
    </DocP>

    <DocH2>Rate limits</DocH2>
    <DocP>Per-desk, per-second, enforced by the sequencer's token-bucket rate limiter:</DocP>
    <DocCode>{`Endpoint / operation            Limit        Burst
place_order                     100/s        200
cancel_order                    500/s        1000
sub / unsub                     20/s         40
REST /account/*                 30/s         60
REST /trades/*                  200/s        400
REST /funding/*                 50/s         100

Global connection cap           4 WS conns per desk cert
REST body size cap              64 KB`}</DocCode>
    <DocP>
      Rate-limit breaches return error code <code style={{ color: COLORS.mint }}>1004</code> on WS
      and HTTP 429 on REST with a <code style={{ color: COLORS.mint }}>Retry-After</code> header.
      Sustained breach triggers a compliance surveillance flag.
    </DocP>

    <DocH2>Error codes</DocH2>
    <DocCode>{`1xxx   Protocol           1001 auth fail · 1002 invalid msg · 1004 rate-limit
2xxx   Trading            2001 margin · 2003 post-only-cross · 2004 leverage
3xxx   Compliance         3001 frozen · 3002 sanctions · 3003 kyc expired
                          3004 position limit · 3005 notional window
4xxx   Chain              4001 unreachable · 4002 bft timeout`}</DocCode>
  </>
);

