const DocsSecurity = () => (
  <>
    <DocH1>Security</DocH1>
    <DocP>
      Onyx is built with the assumption that attackers will try to compromise every layer —
      network, application, key management, and chain. Each layer has its own defensive
      posture and its own audit trail.
    </DocP>

    <DocH2>mTLS &amp; X.509 certificates</DocH2>
    <DocP>
      Every WebSocket connection to the sequencer is mutually authenticated at the TLS layer.
      Your desk's certificate is issued by the JPM internal CA, bound to the LEI, and rotated
      every 90 days. Certificate revocation is immediate via CRL distribution to all
      sequencer nodes.
    </DocP>
    <DocCode>{`# Request a new desk certificate
curl -X POST https://pki.onyx.jpmorgan.com/v1/csr \\
  -H "X-JPM-Auth: $(jpm-auth token)" \\
  --data-binary @desk.csr > desk.crt

# Verify certificate chain
openssl verify -CAfile /etc/ssl/jpm-onyx-root.crt desk.crt`}</DocCode>

    <DocH2>Key management</DocH2>
    <DocP>
      All signing keys — desk signing, validator BLS, JPM Coin bridge — live exclusively
      in FIPS 140-2 Level 3 HSMs (AWS CloudHSM for cloud desks, SafeNet Luna for on-prem).
      Keys never leave the HSM in cleartext. Key usage emits a tamper-evident audit event
      consumed by the SIEM pipeline.
    </DocP>
    <DocNote>
      If your desk cert or HSM PIN is suspected compromised, call the Onyx security hotline
      at +1 (212) 555-0199 to trigger immediate session revocation. Do not email.
    </DocNote>

    <DocH2>Incident response</DocH2>
    <DocP>
      Onyx follows the JPM global CSIRT playbook. Any sev-1 incident (compromised validator,
      leaked key, DoS against the sequencer) triggers an automatic market halt and a
      three-of-five governance quorum for resumption. Post-mortem publication within 5
      business days.
    </DocP>

    <DocH2>Bug bounty</DocH2>
    <DocP>
      Responsible disclosure to <span style={{ color: COLORS.mint }}>security@onyx.jpmorgan.com</span>.
      Rewards up to $500,000 for critical consensus-level findings, $100,000 for sequencer /
      Pact contract findings. Terms and exclusions at <span style={{ color: COLORS.mint }}>onyx.jpmorgan.com/security</span>.
    </DocP>
  </>
);

const DocsGovernance = () => (
  <>
    <DocH1>Governance</DocH1>
    <DocP>
      Onyx is a permissioned system. All protocol-level decisions require a supermajority of
      the validator set or a defined governance quorum. There is no token — governance
      rights flow from JPM's operating agreements and regulator mandates.
    </DocP>

    <DocH2>Validator set</DocH2>
    <DocP>
      21 validators total: 14 operated by JPM, 4 by counterparty banks (Goldman, Morgan
      Stanley, Citi, Bank of America), 3 read-only observer nodes for CFTC, SEC, and FCA.
      Validator changes require 14-of-21 signatures plus Onyx Steering Committee approval.
    </DocP>
    <DocCode>{`# Current validator topology
NY4  ─── 14 validators (writers)
        JPM-NY4-01..14
LD4  ─── 4  validators (writers)
        GS-LD4-01, MS-LD4-01, CITI-LD4-01, BAML-LD4-01
TY3  ─── 3  observers (read-only, regulators)
        CFTC-TY3-01, SEC-TY3-01, FCA-TY3-01`}</DocCode>

    <DocH2>Listing approval</DocH2>
    <DocP>
      New instruments follow a 4-step gate: ECM desk proposes → Compliance reviews position-limit
      and market-integrity risk → Steering Committee signs off → Validator set activates via
      Pact governance transaction on CH-0. Typical timeline 2-4 weeks for crypto, 4-8 for
      physically-settled commodities.
    </DocP>

    <DocH2>Parameter changes</DocH2>
    <DocP>Risk parameters (maintenance margin ratios, leverage caps, liquidation penalty)
      can be changed via a fast-path governance tx signed by 3-of-5 risk officers. Changes
      take effect at the start of the next hour UTC. All changes are immutably logged on CH-0.
    </DocP>

    <DocH2>Emergency halt</DocH2>
    <DocP>
      Any single Onyx officer can halt trading on any instrument within one block (~4ms).
      Halts require 3-of-5 to resume. During a halt, existing positions continue to be marked
      against the oracle price but no new orders match. Margin calls are suspended — no
      liquidations during halt.
    </DocP>
  </>
);

const DocsFaq = () => (
  <>
    <DocH1>Frequently asked questions</DocH1>

    <DocH2>Is Onyx accessible to retail traders?</DocH2>
    <DocP>
      No. Onyx is a strictly institutional venue requiring a valid LEI, passing KYC/AML,
      and a signed participant agreement. Individual traders cannot onboard directly.
    </DocP>

    <DocH2>How fast is order execution really?</DocH2>
    <DocP>
      From "submit" in the UI to optimistic ack: ~1ms (p99) within the NY4 metro.
      From submit to BFT-finalized: ~5ms (p99). Cross-chain settlement (match → JPM Coin
      debit/credit) adds another ~10ms. These are production numbers measured over the
      last 30 days.
    </DocP>

    <DocH2>What happens during a BFT validator failure?</DocH2>
    <DocP>
      HotStuff tolerates up to 6 Byzantine validators (out of 21) without loss of safety or
      liveness. If more than 6 fail simultaneously, the chain halts until operators restore
      at least 15 honest nodes. No funds can be lost during a halt — positions are frozen
      at the last finalized block.
    </DocP>

    <DocH2>Can I trade when the US markets are closed?</DocH2>
    <DocP>
      Crypto perpetuals trade 24/7. Oil and energy futures follow CME trading hours —
      Sunday 18:00 ET through Friday 17:00 ET, with a 60-minute daily maintenance window
      17:00-18:00 ET. Physical delivery requests must be submitted 5 business days before
      contract expiry.
    </DocP>

    <DocH2>How does JPM Coin settlement differ from USDC?</DocH2>
    <DocP>
      JPM Coin is a direct claim on a regulated US bank deposit — not a stablecoin. It is
      100% reserved, FDIC-insured up to applicable limits, and does not depend on any
      third-party issuer. Conversion to USD via Fedwire is immediate and free within JPM,
      typically next-day to other banks.
    </DocP>

    <DocH2>What is the difference between ECM-147 and my LEI?</DocH2>
    <DocP>
      Your LEI identifies your legal entity globally (ISO 17442). Your desk code (e.g. ECM-147)
      identifies a specific trading book within your firm. One LEI can have many desk codes,
      each with its own book-level risk limits and P&amp;L.
    </DocP>

    <DocH2>Contact</DocH2>
    <DocP>
      Onboarding: <span style={{ color: COLORS.mint }}>onyx-onboarding@jpmorgan.com</span><br />
      Trading support (24x7): <span style={{ color: COLORS.mint }}>onyx-trading@jpmorgan.com</span> · +1 (212) 555-0100<br />
      Security: <span style={{ color: COLORS.mint }}>security@onyx.jpmorgan.com</span><br />
      Status page: <span style={{ color: COLORS.mint }}>status.onyx.jpmorgan.com</span>
    </DocP>
  </>
);

/* ════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
   WATCHLIST PAGE
   ════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════ */

// Mini price feed used inside watchlist cards — lightweight, shares the same
// data sources as the full usePriceFeed but without the drift ticker overhead
// for better performance when rendering many cards at once.
const WatchlistCard = ({ instrument, onSelect, onToggleWatch }) => {
  const feed = usePriceFeed(instrument);
  const change = feed.change24h ?? instrument.change24h;
  const up = change >= 0;
  return (
    <div
      className="rounded-md border p-4 transition-colors hover:bg-white/[0.02]"
      style={{ background: COLORS.surface, borderColor: COLORS.border }}
    >
      <div className="flex items-start justify-between mb-3">
        <button
          onClick={() => onSelect(instrument)}
          className="flex items-center gap-2 text-left min-w-0"
        >
          <InstIcon cls={instrument.cls} size={18} ticker={instrument.id} />
          <div className="leading-tight min-w-0">
            <div className="text-[14px] font-medium truncate" style={{ color: COLORS.text }}>
              {instrument.id}
            </div>
            <div className="text-[11px] truncate" style={{ color: COLORS.textMute }}>
              {instrument.name}
            </div>
          </div>
        </button>
        <button
          onClick={() => onToggleWatch(instrument.id)}
          className="shrink-0 transition-transform"
          title="Remove from watchlist"
        >
          <Star size={14} style={{ color: COLORS.mint, fill: COLORS.mint }} />
        </button>
      </div>

      <button
        onClick={() => onSelect(instrument)}
        className="block w-full text-left"
      >
        <div className="text-[22px] tabular-nums" style={{ color: COLORS.text }}>
          {fmt(feed.price, instrument.dec)}
        </div>
        <div className="flex items-center gap-3 mt-1.5">
          <div className="flex items-center gap-1 text-[12px] tabular-nums"
               style={{ color: up ? COLORS.green : COLORS.red }}>
            {up ? <ArrowUpRight size={12} /> : <ArrowDownRight size={12} />}
            <span>{up ? '+' : ''}{change.toFixed(2)}%</span>
          </div>
          <span className="text-[10px]" style={{ color: COLORS.textMute }}>
            Vol {fmtCompact(instrument.vol24h)}
          </span>
        </div>
      </button>
    </div>
  );
};

// Detailed watchlist card — mirrors the multi-metric layout from broker
// research apps. Shows mini sparkline + key metrics (volume, sizzle, yield,
// P/E, beta, EPS) in a compact grid, similar to TradingView/Magnifi UIs.
const WatchlistDetailCard = ({ instrument, onSelect, onToggleWatch }) => {
  const feed = usePriceFeed(instrument);
  const change = feed.change24h ?? instrument.change24h;
  const up = change >= 0;
  // Synthesize mini-sparkline (24 points, ending at current price)
  const seed = (instrument.id || 'X').split('').reduce((a, c) => a + c.charCodeAt(0), 0);
  const spark = useMemo(() => {
    const points = 24;
    const out = [];
    const startPx = (feed.price ?? instrument.mark) * (1 - (change / 100));
    for (let i = 0; i < points; i++) {
      const noise = Math.sin((seed + i) * 1.7) * (instrument.mark * 0.005);
      const t = i / (points - 1);
      out.push(startPx + (feed.price - startPx) * t + noise);
    }
    return out;
  }, [feed.price, instrument.mark, change, seed]);

  // Compute mini metrics
  const yld = TICKER_DIVIDEND_YIELDS?.[instrument.id] ?? 0;
  const beta = TICKER_BETAS?.[instrument.id] ?? 1.0;
  const sizzle = +(0.3 + ((seed % 20) / 20) * 1.2).toFixed(2);    // 0.3 - 1.5
  const pe = instrument.cls === 'equity' ? +(8 + (seed % 35)).toFixed(1) : null;
  const eps = instrument.cls === 'equity' ? +((feed.price / Math.max(pe ?? 1, 1))).toFixed(2) : null;
  const volI = +(0.4 + ((seed % 30) / 30) * 2.2).toFixed(2);

  // Sparkline path
  const min = Math.min(...spark), max = Math.max(...spark);
  const span = max - min || 1;
  const sparkPath = spark.map((p, i) => {
    const x = (i / (spark.length - 1)) * 100;
    const y = 100 - ((p - min) / span) * 100;
    return `${i === 0 ? 'M' : 'L'} ${x.toFixed(1)} ${y.toFixed(1)}`;
  }).join(' ');

  return (
    <div className="rounded-md border p-3 hover:bg-white/[0.02] transition-colors cursor-pointer"
         style={{ background: COLORS.surface, borderColor: COLORS.border }}
         onClick={() => onSelect(instrument)}>
      <div className="flex items-start gap-3">
        {/* Left: ticker + price + sparkline */}
        <div className="flex flex-col items-start gap-1.5 shrink-0" style={{ width: 100 }}>
          <div className="flex items-center gap-1.5 w-full">
            <InstIcon cls={instrument.cls} size={14} ticker={instrument.id} />
            <span className="text-[12px] font-medium truncate" style={{ color: COLORS.text }}>{instrument.id}</span>
          </div>
          <div className="text-[14px] tabular-nums font-medium" style={{ color: COLORS.text }}>
            {fmt(feed.price, instrument.dec)}
          </div>
          <div className="text-[10.5px] tabular-nums" style={{ color: up ? COLORS.green : COLORS.red }}>
            {up ? '+' : ''}{change.toFixed(2)}%
          </div>
          {/* Sparkline */}
          <svg viewBox="0 0 100 30" className="w-full h-6" preserveAspectRatio="none">
            <path d={sparkPath.replace(/y/g, '')}
                  fill="none"
                  stroke={up ? COLORS.green : COLORS.red}
                  strokeWidth="1.5"
                  vectorEffect="non-scaling-stroke" />
          </svg>
        </div>
        {/* Right: metrics grid */}
        <div className="flex-1 grid grid-cols-2 gap-x-3 gap-y-1 text-[10.5px]">
          <div className="flex justify-between"><span style={{ color: COLORS.textMute }}>Volume</span><span className="tabular-nums" style={{ color: COLORS.text }}>{fmtCompact(instrument.vol24h)}</span></div>
          <div className="flex justify-between"><span style={{ color: COLORS.textMute }}>Beta</span><span className="tabular-nums" style={{ color: COLORS.text }}>{beta.toFixed(2)}</span></div>
          <div className="flex justify-between"><span style={{ color: COLORS.textMute }}>Sizzle</span><span className="tabular-nums" style={{ color: COLORS.text }}>{sizzle}</span></div>
          <div className="flex justify-between"><span style={{ color: COLORS.textMute }}>Yield</span><span className="tabular-nums" style={{ color: yld > 0.03 ? COLORS.mint : COLORS.text }}>{yld > 0 ? `${(yld * 100).toFixed(2)}%` : '—'}</span></div>
          <div className="flex justify-between"><span style={{ color: COLORS.textMute }}>Vol I</span><span className="tabular-nums" style={{ color: COLORS.text }}>{volI}</span></div>
          {pe !== null ? (
            <div className="flex justify-between"><span style={{ color: COLORS.textMute }}>P/E</span><span className="tabular-nums" style={{ color: COLORS.text }}>{pe.toFixed(1)}</span></div>
          ) : (
            <div className="flex justify-between"><span style={{ color: COLORS.textMute }}>OI</span><span className="tabular-nums" style={{ color: COLORS.text }}>{fmtCompact(instrument.oi)}</span></div>
          )}
          {eps !== null && (
            <>
              <div className="flex justify-between"><span style={{ color: COLORS.textMute }}>P/C Ratio</span><span className="tabular-nums" style={{ color: COLORS.text }}>{(0.5 + ((seed % 15) / 15)).toFixed(3)}</span></div>
              <div className="flex justify-between"><span style={{ color: COLORS.textMute }}>EPS</span><span className="tabular-nums" style={{ color: COLORS.text }}>{eps}</span></div>
            </>
          )}
        </div>
        <button onClick={(e) => { e.stopPropagation(); onToggleWatch(instrument.id); }}
                className="shrink-0 transition-transform"
                title="Remove from watchlist">
          <Star size={12} style={{ color: COLORS.mint, fill: COLORS.mint }} />
        </button>
      </div>
    </div>
  );
};

// WatchlistDiscoverySections — Yahoo Finance / Bloomberg-style "what's
// moving" lists rendered below the user's watched tickers. Three
// lists side by side at desktop, stacked on mobile:
//   - Highest volume (top vol24h)
//   - Most volatile (largest |change24h|)
//   - Most active gainers (positive change24h descending)
// Pulls from the existing INSTRUMENTS catalog so data lines up with
// the rest of the app. Click a row to set it as active; click the
// star to add to the user's main watchlist.
const WatchlistDiscoverySections = ({ onSelect, watchedTickers = [], onAdd }) => {
  const equities = useMemo(
    () => INSTRUMENTS.filter(i => i.cls === 'equity' && Number.isFinite(i.vol24h) && Number.isFinite(i.change24h)),
    []
  );
  const highestVolume = useMemo(
    () => [...equities].sort((a, b) => (b.vol24h || 0) - (a.vol24h || 0)).slice(0, 6),
    [equities]
  );
  const mostVolatile = useMemo(
    () => [...equities].sort((a, b) => Math.abs(b.change24h || 0) - Math.abs(a.change24h || 0)).slice(0, 6),
    [equities]
  );
  const topGainers = useMemo(
    () => [...equities].sort((a, b) => (b.change24h || 0) - (a.change24h || 0)).slice(0, 6),
    [equities]
  );
  const sections = [
    { key: 'volume',   title: 'Highest volume stocks',  data: highestVolume, hint: 'vol' },
    { key: 'volatile', title: 'Most volatile stocks',   data: mostVolatile,  hint: 'abs%' },
    { key: 'gainers',  title: 'Top gainers',            data: topGainers,    hint: '%' },
  ];
  return (
    <div className="mt-10 grid grid-cols-1 lg:grid-cols-3 gap-6">
      {sections.map(sec => (
        <div key={sec.key} className="rounded-md p-4"
             style={{ background: COLORS.surface, border: `1px solid ${COLORS.border}` }}>
          <div className="flex items-center justify-between mb-3">
            <h3 className="text-[14px] font-semibold" style={{ color: COLORS.text }}>{sec.title}</h3>
          </div>
          <div className="space-y-1">
            {sec.data.map(inst => {
              const watched = watchedTickers.includes(inst.id);
              const change = inst.change24h ?? 0;
              const positive = change >= 0;
              return (
                <div key={inst.id}
                     className="flex items-center gap-3 px-2 py-2 rounded transition-colors hover:bg-white/[0.03] cursor-pointer"
                     onClick={() => onSelect?.(inst)}>
                  <InstIcon cls={inst.cls} ticker={inst.id} size={28} />
                  <div className="flex-1 min-w-0">
                    <div className="text-[12.5px] font-medium truncate" style={{ color: COLORS.text }}>
                      {inst.name}
                    </div>
                    <div className="text-[10px] tabular-nums" style={{ color: COLORS.textMute }}>
                      {inst.id}
                    </div>
                  </div>
                  <div className="text-right shrink-0">
                    <div className="text-[12.5px] tabular-nums" style={{ color: COLORS.text }}>
                      {(inst.mark ?? 0).toFixed(2)} <span className="text-[9.5px]" style={{ color: COLORS.textMute }}>USD</span>
                    </div>
                    <div className="text-[11px] tabular-nums"
                         style={{ color: positive ? COLORS.green : COLORS.red }}>
                      {positive ? '+' : ''}{change.toFixed(2)}%
                    </div>
                  </div>
                  <button onClick={(e) => { e.stopPropagation(); onAdd?.(inst.id); }}
                          className="w-6 h-6 rounded flex items-center justify-center transition-colors hover:bg-white/[0.06]"
                          style={{ color: watched ? COLORS.mint : COLORS.textMute }}
                          title={watched ? 'In your watchlist' : 'Add to watchlist'}>
                    {watched ? '★' : '☆'}
                  </button>
                </div>
              );
            })}
          </div>
        </div>
      ))}
    </div>
  );
};

const WatchlistPage = ({ account, user, onSelect, onToggleWatch, onAddMarket }) => {
  const STORAGE_KEY = `imo_watchlists_${user?.username ?? 'guest'}`;
  // Default — one list called "Main" populated from account.watchlist
  const [lists, setLists] = useState(() => {
    try {
      const raw = localStorage.getItem(STORAGE_KEY);
      if (raw) return JSON.parse(raw);
    } catch {}
    return [{ id: 'main', name: 'Main', tickers: account?.watchlist ?? [] }];
  });
  const [activeListId, setActiveListId] = useState(() => lists[0]?.id ?? 'main');
  const [renaming, setRenaming] = useState(null);
  const [newListName, setNewListName] = useState('');
  // Inline ticker search — adds to the active list without redirecting
  const [tickerQuery, setTickerQuery] = useState('');
  const [searchOpen, setSearchOpen] = useState(false);
  // View mode: compact list, cards (default), or detailed metric tiles
  const [watchView, setWatchView] = useState('cards');
  const [screenerOpen, setScreenerOpen] = useState(false);

  const persist = (next) => {
    setLists(next);
    try { localStorage.setItem(STORAGE_KEY, JSON.stringify(next)); } catch {}
  };

  // Sync the canonical account.watchlist into the "Main" list when it changes
  useEffect(() => {
    if (!account?.watchlist) return;
    setLists(prev => {
      const idx = prev.findIndex(l => l.id === 'main');
      if (idx < 0) return prev;
      // Merge: any ticker on canonical watchlist appears in main
      const next = [...prev];
      const merged = Array.from(new Set([...next[idx].tickers, ...account.watchlist]));
      next[idx] = { ...next[idx], tickers: merged };
      return next;
    });
  }, [account?.watchlist?.length]);

  const activeList = lists.find(l => l.id === activeListId) ?? lists[0];
  const watched = INSTRUMENTS.filter(i => activeList?.tickers?.includes(i.id));

  const addList = () => {
    const name = (newListName || `List ${lists.length + 1}`).trim();
    const id = name.toLowerCase().replace(/[^a-z0-9]+/g, '-').slice(0, 24) || `list-${Date.now()}`;
    if (lists.some(l => l.id === id)) return;
    persist([...lists, { id, name, tickers: [] }]);
    setActiveListId(id);
    setNewListName('');
    setRenaming(null);
  };

  const removeList = (id) => {
    if (id === 'main') return; // can't delete the main list
    const next = lists.filter(l => l.id !== id);
    persist(next);
    if (activeListId === id) setActiveListId('main');
  };

  const removeFromList = (ticker) => {
    if (!activeList) return;
    const next = lists.map(l =>
      l.id === activeList.id ? { ...l, tickers: l.tickers.filter(t => t !== ticker) } : l
    );
    persist(next);
    // Also call onToggleWatch if it's the main list (keeps account state in sync)
    if (activeList.id === 'main') onToggleWatch?.(ticker);
  };

  return (
    <div className="flex-1 overflow-y-auto" style={{ background: COLORS.bg }}>
      <div className="max-w-6xl mx-auto px-8 py-10">
        <div className="flex items-center justify-between mb-6">
          <div>
            <h1 className="text-[24px] font-medium mb-1" style={{ color: COLORS.text }}>Watchlists</h1>
            <p className="text-[13px]" style={{ color: COLORS.textMute }}>
              Organize markets into multiple themed lists.
            </p>
          </div>
          <div className="relative">
            <button
              onClick={() => setSearchOpen(o => !o)}
              className="flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-2 rounded-md text-[13px] font-medium transition-all hover:opacity-90"
              style={{ background: COLORS.mint, color: COLORS.bg }}
            >
              <Plus size={14} />
              Add market
            </button>
            {searchOpen && (
              <>
                <div className="fixed inset-0 z-30" onClick={() => { setSearchOpen(false); setTickerQuery(''); }} />
                <div className="absolute right-0 top-full mt-2 z-40 w-80 rounded-md border overflow-hidden"
                     style={{ background: COLORS.surface, borderColor: COLORS.borderHi, boxShadow: '0 8px 24px rgba(0,0,0,0.4)' }}>
                  <input value={tickerQuery}
                         onChange={e => setTickerQuery(e.target.value)}
                         autoFocus
                         placeholder="Search ticker (AAPL, BTC-PERP, etc.)"
                         className="w-full px-3 py-2.5 text-[12.5px] outline-none border-b"
                         style={{ background: COLORS.bg, color: COLORS.text, borderColor: COLORS.border }} />
                  <div className="max-h-72 overflow-y-auto">
                    {(() => {
                      const q = tickerQuery.trim().toLowerCase();
                      const candidates = INSTRUMENTS
                        .filter(i => !q || i.id.toLowerCase().includes(q) || i.name.toLowerCase().includes(q))
                        .filter(i => !activeList?.tickers?.includes(i.id))
                        .slice(0, 50);
                      if (candidates.length === 0) {
                        return (
                          <div className="py-6 text-center text-[11px]" style={{ color: COLORS.textMute }}>
                            {q ? 'No matching markets' : 'All markets already on this list'}
                          </div>
                        );
                      }
                      return candidates.map(inst => (
                        <button key={inst.id}
                                onClick={() => {
                                  // Add to active list inline — DON'T redirect to trade
                                  const next = lists.map(l =>
                                    l.id === activeListId
                                      ? { ...l, tickers: [...(l.tickers ?? []), inst.id] }
                                      : l
                                  );
                                  persist(next);
                                  // Also add to canonical watchlist if Main
                                  if (activeListId === 'main') onToggleWatch?.(inst.id);
                                  setTickerQuery('');
                                }}
                                className="w-full px-3 py-2 text-left flex items-center justify-between hover:bg-white/[0.04] border-b last:border-b-0"
                                style={{ borderColor: COLORS.border }}>
                          <div>
                            <div className="text-[12px] font-medium" style={{ color: COLORS.text }}>{formatTicker(inst.id, inst.cls)}</div>
                            <div className="text-[10px]" style={{ color: COLORS.textMute }}>{inst.name}</div>
                          </div>
                          <span className="text-[11px] tabular-nums" style={{ color: COLORS.textDim }}>
                            ${inst.mark?.toFixed(inst.dec ?? 2) ?? '—'}
                          </span>
                        </button>
                      ));
                    })()}
                  </div>
                </div>
              </>
            )}
          </div>
        </div>

        {/* List tabs */}
        <div className="flex items-center gap-1 mb-5 flex-wrap">
          {lists.map(l => (
            <div key={l.id} className="flex items-center gap-1 group">
              <button onClick={() => setActiveListId(l.id)}
                      className="px-3 py-1.5 rounded-md text-[12px] transition-colors"
                      style={{
                        background: activeListId === l.id ? COLORS.surface : 'transparent',
                        color: activeListId === l.id ? COLORS.text : COLORS.textDim,
                        border: `1px solid ${activeListId === l.id ? COLORS.mint : COLORS.border}`,
                      }}>
                {l.name} <span className="ml-1 text-[10px] tabular-nums" style={{ color: COLORS.textMute }}>{l.tickers.length}</span>
              </button>
              {l.id !== 'main' && activeListId === l.id && (
                <button onClick={() => removeList(l.id)}
                        title={`Delete list "${l.name}"`}
                        className="p-1 rounded hover:bg-white/[0.05]">
                  <X size={11} style={{ color: COLORS.textMute }} />
                </button>
              )}
            </div>
          ))}
          {renaming === 'new' ? (
            <div className="flex items-center gap-1">
              <input autoFocus value={newListName}
                     onChange={e => setNewListName(e.target.value.slice(0, 24))}
                     onKeyDown={e => e.key === 'Enter' && addList()}
                     placeholder="List name"
                     className="px-2 py-1.5 rounded-md text-[12px] outline-none w-32"
                     style={{ background: COLORS.surface, color: COLORS.text, border: `1px solid ${COLORS.mint}` }} />
              <button onClick={addList}
                      className="px-2 py-1.5 rounded text-[11px] font-medium"
                      style={{ background: COLORS.mint, color: COLORS.bg }}>Add</button>
              <button onClick={() => { setRenaming(null); setNewListName(''); }}
                      className="px-2 py-1.5 rounded text-[11px]"
                      style={{ color: COLORS.textDim }}>Cancel</button>
            </div>
          ) : (
            <button onClick={() => setRenaming('new')}
                    className="px-3 py-1.5 rounded-md text-[12px] flex items-center gap-1"
                    style={{ color: COLORS.mint, border: `1px dashed ${COLORS.border}` }}
                    title="Create a new watchlist">
              <Plus size={11} />
              New list
            </button>
          )}
        </div>

        {watched.length === 0 ? (
          <div className="rounded-md border py-16 px-6 text-center"
               style={{ background: COLORS.surface, borderColor: COLORS.border }}>
            <div className="w-12 h-12 rounded-full flex items-center justify-center mx-auto mb-4"
                 style={{ background: COLORS.surface2 }}>
              <Star size={20} style={{ color: COLORS.textMute }} />
            </div>
            <div className="text-[15px] mb-2" style={{ color: COLORS.text }}>
              "{activeList?.name}" is empty
            </div>
            <div className="text-[12px] max-w-md mx-auto mb-5" style={{ color: COLORS.textMute }}>
              Add markets to this list. Tickers can appear in multiple lists.
            </div>
            <div className="flex items-center justify-center gap-2 flex-wrap">
              <button
                onClick={() => setScreenerOpen(true)}
                className="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-4 py-2 rounded-md text-[13px] font-medium transition-all hover:bg-white/[0.04]"
                style={{ background: COLORS.surface, color: COLORS.text, border: `1px solid ${COLORS.border}` }}
                title="Open the Market Scanner — filter stocks by sector, P/E, market cap, momentum"
              >
                Market Scanner
              </button>
              <button
                onClick={() => setSearchOpen(true)}
                className="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-4 py-2 rounded-md text-[13px] font-medium transition-all hover:opacity-90"
                style={{ background: COLORS.mint, color: COLORS.bg }}
              >
                <Search size={14} />
                Browse markets
              </button>
            </div>
          </div>
        ) : (
          <>
            {/* View mode toggle + Market screener + Add market */}
            <div className="flex items-center justify-between mb-3 gap-2 flex-wrap">
              <div className="flex items-center gap-2">
                <button onClick={() => setScreenerOpen(true)}
                        className="px-3 py-1.5 rounded-md text-[12px] font-medium transition-colors hover:opacity-90"
                        style={{ background: COLORS.surface, color: COLORS.text, border: `1px solid ${COLORS.border}` }}
                        title="Filter stocks by criteria like P/E, market cap, sector, dividend yield">
                  Market Scanner
                </button>
                {/* + Add market — opens the instrument picker so user can
                    quickly add a ticker to the watchlist without scrolling
                    through the scanner results. */}
                <button onClick={() => onAddMarket?.()}
                        className="px-3 py-1.5 rounded-md text-[12px] font-medium transition-all hover:bg-white/[0.04]"
                        style={{
                          // Apple liquid-glass treatment: dark interior with
                          // a subtle blur, blue border + blue text. Reads as
                          // an action without the heavy primary-button bg.
                          background: 'rgba(20, 26, 36, 0.6)',
                          color: COLORS.mint,
                          border: `1px solid ${COLORS.mint}`,
                          backdropFilter: 'blur(10px) saturate(180%)',
                          WebkitBackdropFilter: 'blur(10px) saturate(180%)',
                          boxShadow:
                            `0 1px 0 rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.08) inset, ` +
                            `0 4px 12px rgba(42, 74, 127, 0.18)`,
                        }}
                        title="Add a market or instrument to your watchlist">
                  + Add market
                </button>
              </div>
              <div className="flex items-center gap-2">
                <span className="text-[10px] uppercase tracking-wider" style={{ color: COLORS.textMute }}>View</span>
                <div className="flex items-center gap-0.5 p-0.5 rounded" style={{ background: COLORS.surface }}>
                {[
                  { id: 'compact', label: '☰ Compact' },
                  { id: 'cards',   label: '▦ Cards' },
                  { id: 'detail',  label: '◰ Detailed' },
                ].map(v => (
                  <button key={v.id} onClick={() => setWatchView(v.id)}
                          className="px-2 py-1 text-[10.5px] rounded transition-colors"
                          style={{
                            background: watchView === v.id ? COLORS.mint : 'transparent',
                            color: watchView === v.id ? COLORS.bg : COLORS.textDim,
                          }}>{v.label}</button>
                ))}
              </div>
              </div>
            </div>

            {/* Group watched by class for sectioned display */}
            {(() => {
              const byClass = { equity: [], crypto: [], energy: [], metal: [] };
              watched.forEach(inst => {
                if (byClass[inst.cls]) byClass[inst.cls].push(inst);
              });
              const SECTION_LABELS = {
                equity:  { label: 'Stocks & ETFs', icon: '📈' },
                crypto:  { label: 'Crypto',         icon: '₿' },
                energy:  { label: 'Futures · Energy', icon: '🛢' },
                metal:   { label: 'Futures · Metals', icon: '🪙' },
              };
              const sectionsToShow = ['equity', 'crypto', 'energy', 'metal'].filter(c => byClass[c].length > 0);
              return sectionsToShow.map(cls => (
                <div key={cls} className="mb-6">
                  <div className="flex items-center justify-between mb-2 px-1">
                    <div className="flex items-center gap-2">
                      <span style={{ fontSize: 14 }}>{SECTION_LABELS[cls].icon}</span>
                      <h2 className="text-[11px] uppercase tracking-wider font-medium" style={{ color: COLORS.textMute }}>
                        {SECTION_LABELS[cls].label}
                      </h2>
                      <span className="text-[10px] px-1.5 py-0.5 rounded" style={{ background: COLORS.surface, color: COLORS.textDim }}>
                        {byClass[cls].length}
                      </span>
                    </div>
                  </div>
                  {watchView === 'compact' ? (
                    <div className="rounded-md border overflow-hidden" style={{ borderColor: COLORS.border, background: COLORS.surface }}>
                      {byClass[cls].map((inst, i) => (
                        <button key={inst.id}
                                onClick={() => onSelect(inst)}
                                className="w-full flex items-center gap-3 px-3 py-2.5 hover:bg-white/[0.04] border-b last:border-b-0 transition-colors"
                                style={{ borderColor: COLORS.border }}>
                          <SectorLetter cls={inst.cls} size={20} />
                          <InstIcon cls={inst.cls} ticker={inst.id} size={28} />
                          <div className="flex-1 min-w-0 text-left">
                            <div className="text-[12.5px] font-medium" style={{ color: COLORS.text }}>{formatTicker(inst.id, inst.cls)}</div>
                            <div className="text-[10.5px] truncate" style={{ color: COLORS.textMute }}>{inst.name}</div>
                          </div>
                          <div className="text-right shrink-0">
                            <div className="text-[12.5px] tabular-nums" style={{ color: COLORS.text }}>
                              ${inst.mark?.toFixed(inst.dec ?? 2)}
                            </div>
                            <div className="text-[10.5px] tabular-nums" style={{ color: (inst.change24h ?? 0) >= 0 ? COLORS.green : COLORS.red }}>
                              {(inst.change24h ?? 0) >= 0 ? '+' : ''}{(inst.change24h ?? 0).toFixed(2)}%
                            </div>
                          </div>
                          <button onClick={(e) => { e.stopPropagation(); removeFromList(inst.id); }}
                                  className="text-[10px] px-1.5 py-0.5 rounded hover:bg-white/[0.05]"
                                  style={{ color: COLORS.textMute }}
                                  title="Remove from list">×</button>
                        </button>
                      ))}
                    </div>
                  ) : watchView === 'detail' ? (
                    <div className="grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-2">
                      {byClass[cls].map(inst => (
                        <WatchlistDetailCard key={inst.id} instrument={inst}
                                             onSelect={onSelect}
                                             onToggleWatch={() => removeFromList(inst.id)} />
                      ))}
                    </div>
                  ) : (
                    <div className="grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-3 gap-4">
                      {byClass[cls].map(inst => (
                        <WatchlistCard key={inst.id} instrument={inst}
                                       onSelect={onSelect}
                                       onToggleWatch={() => removeFromList(inst.id)} />
                      ))}
                    </div>
                  )}
                </div>
              ));
            })()}
            {/* ─── Discovery sections ──────────────────────────────────
                Below the user's watched tickers we surface two
                Yahoo-Finance-style lists: highest volume and most
                volatile (largest |% change|). Pulled from the same
                INSTRUMENTS catalog so the data comes from the same
                feed the rest of the app uses; click a row to make
                that instrument active, click the star to add to the
                user's main watchlist. Helps users find new tickers
                without leaving the page. */}
            <WatchlistDiscoverySections
              onSelect={onSelect}
              watchedTickers={activeList?.tickers ?? []}
              onAdd={(ticker) => {
                const next = lists.map(l =>
                  l.id === activeListId
                    ? { ...l, tickers: [...new Set([...(l.tickers ?? []), ticker])] }
                    : l
                );
                persist(next);
                if (activeListId === 'main') onToggleWatch?.(ticker);
              }} />
          </>
        )}
      </div>
      {screenerOpen && (
        <MarketScreenerModal onClose={() => setScreenerOpen(false)}
                             onAdd={(ticker) => {
                               const next = lists.map(l =>
                                 l.id === activeListId
                                   ? { ...l, tickers: [...new Set([...(l.tickers ?? []), ticker])] }
                                   : l
                               );
                               persist(next);
                               if (activeListId === 'main') onToggleWatch?.(ticker);
                             }}
                             onSelect={onSelect}
                             watchedTickers={activeList?.tickers ?? []} />
      )}
    </div>
  );
};

// ──────────── Market Screener Modal ────────────
